kind.prompt:
You are implementing features for a Blazor Web App shipment tracker at /tmp/sv-38da10e02cd941b59312973f90060fea/ShipmentTracker. The project uses Interactive Auto Global mode with Individual authentication. It has two projects: ShipmentTracker (server) and ShipmentTracker.Client (WebAssembly).

The app needs:
1. A Shipment model and data
2. A shared service interface in the Client project
3. Server implementation using EF Core, client implementation using HttpClient
4. API endpoints on the server
5. Dispatcher page: shows list of all shipments with status, destination, and ability to update status
6. Customer page: lets customers enter a tracking number to check status and estimated delivery
7. Role-based authorization: Dispatchers see the dispatcher page, customers see the tracking page

Here's what already exists:
- Server Program.cs has Identity, EF Core with SQLite, and all the Auto mode wiring
- Client Program.cs has auth deserialization set up
- The ApplicationDbContext is at ShipmentTracker.Data.ApplicationDbContext
- The ApplicationUser is at ShipmentTracker.Data.ApplicationUser

Please do the following:

### 1. Create the Shipment model in the Server project

Create file: /tmp/sv-38da10e02cd941b59312973f90060fea/ShipmentTracker/ShipmentTracker/Data/Shipment.cs

```csharp
namespace ShipmentTracker.Data;

public class Shipment
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public string TrackingNumber { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Origin { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Destination { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public ShipmentStatus Status { get; set; }
    public DateTime CreatedDate { get; set; }
    public DateTime EstimatedDelivery { get; set; }
    public string CustomerEmail { get; set; } = string.Empty;
}

public enum ShipmentStatus
{
    Pending,
    PickedUp,
    InTransit,
    OutForDelivery,
    Delivered,
    Exception
}
```

